    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SR periodicity selection in TDD configurations\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_SR_periodandoffset()` function in nr_rrc_config.c was not correctly mapping subcarrier spacing enum values to the appropriate slots per frame array indices. This caused incorrect SR periodicity selection, particularly in TDD configurations where the first UL slot calculation was not properly bounded by the selected periodicity.\n\nThis fix implements proper mapping from subcarrier spacing enum values to slotsperframe array indices and ensures the SR offset is always less than the periodicity.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`: \n  - Replaced flawed conditional logic with proper enum-to-index mapping\n  - Added bounds checking for subcarrier spacing values\n  - Ensured SR offset is properly bounded using modulo operation\n  - Improved function clarity with better comments\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a gNB with TDD UL/DL pattern\n2. Set subcarrier spacing to 30 kHz or higher\n3. Observe that SR periodicity is incorrectly set to sl10 instead of appropriate value\n4. UE may miss SR opportunities or experience collisions due to incorrect timing\n\nThe fix ensures proper SR periodicity selection based on actual subcarrier spacing and TDD configuration parameters.\n"
}